---
import PageLayout from "../../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
import Modal from "../../components/Modal.astro";
import { siteConfig, pageAssetUrl } from "../../config/site";
import { landingContent } from "../../data/locales";

const content = landingContent.en;
const routePath = "/blog/how-to-track-learning-progress/";
const heroImage = pageAssetUrl(routePath, "assets/card-2.png");
---

<PageLayout
  title="How to Track Learning Progress — Fluxo"
  description="Most people measure learning the wrong way. They count hours spent studying, books finished, or pages read. These numbers feel meaningful but they measure input, not output."
  canonicalPath="/blog/how-to-track-learning-progress/"
  routePath={routePath}
  lang="en"
>
  <Header content={content} routePath={routePath} />

  <main class="article-page">
    <article class="article">

      <div class="article-header">
        <p class="article-category">Knowledge Hub</p>
        <h1 class="article-title">How to Track Learning Progress?</h1>
        <p class="article-subtitle">Most people measure learning the wrong way. They count hours spent studying, books finished, or pages read. These numbers feel meaningful but they measure input, not output.</p>
        <div class="article-meta">
          <span>Fluxo Team</span>
          <span class="article-meta-dot">·</span>
          <span>4 min read</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="article-hero">
        <img src={heroImage} alt="How to track learning progress" />
      </div>

      <div class="article-body">

        <p>The real question is: how much do you actually retain?</p>

        <hr class="article-rule" />

        <h2>Why Most Tracking Fails</h2>

        <p>Time spent studying has almost no correlation with how much you remember. A 2006 study by <a href="https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.1467-9280.2006.01693.x" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Roediger and Karpicke at Washington University</a> demonstrated this directly: two groups of students spent identical time with the same material. One group re-read it. The other tested themselves. A week later, the self-testing group remembered significantly more, even though they "studied" less in the traditional sense.</p>

        <p>Hours logged doesn't tell you whether learning happened. Recall does.</p>

        <hr class="article-rule" />

        <h2>What's Actually Worth Measuring</h2>

        <p><strong>Retention rate</strong></p>

        <p>Can you retrieve this information without looking at it? That's the only metric that matters for long-term learning. Everything else — time, completion, highlights — is a proxy that often misleads you into thinking you've learned more than you have.</p>

        <p><strong>Recall difficulty over time</strong></p>

        <p>How hard is it to remember something after one day? After one week? After one month? If recall gets easier over time with shorter sessions, the knowledge is consolidating. If it stays hard, you need more repetition or a different approach. Tracking this across topics gives you real signal about what's working.</p>

        <p><strong>Gaps, not just wins</strong></p>

        <p>Most progress tracking shows you what you've completed. More useful is tracking what you've forgotten or gotten wrong. A system that surfaces your weakest areas and prioritizes them in review sessions is more valuable than one that tracks streaks and badges.</p>

        <hr class="article-rule" />

        <h2>The Problem With Manual Tracking</h2>

        <p>You can build a spreadsheet to track all of this. Some people do. Most stop after two weeks because maintaining it takes as much energy as the learning itself.</p>

        <p>The value of tracking learning progress is real — MIT's Teaching and Learning Lab <a href="https://tll.mit.edu/teaching-resources/how-people-learn/metacognition/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">notes that metacognitive monitoring</a> significantly improves learning outcomes. Knowing where you are, what's fading, and what needs attention lets you direct your effort where it matters. But that only works if the tracking is automatic.</p>

        <hr class="article-rule" />

        <h2>What Automatic Progress Tracking Looks Like</h2>

        <p><strong><a href="/">Fluxo</a></strong> tracks retention by measuring how you perform during each review session. Every time you recall something correctly or struggle with it, Fluxo adjusts its model of what you know. Over time, you can see your retention rate by topic — not how many notes you have, but how much of that material you can actually recall.</p>

        <p>This turns progress tracking from a chore into something that just happens as you learn. You study, Fluxo measures, and at any point you can see clearly which subjects are solid and which need more work.</p>

        <p>Learning without tracking is flying blind. Tracking without recall measurement tells you the wrong things. Fluxo does both.</p>

        <button type="button" class="btn-primary" data-modal-open data-from="article-cta">Start for free</button>

      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer content={content} routePath={routePath} />
  <Modal content={content} />
</PageLayout>

<script define:vars={{ leadsUrl: `${siteConfig.leadsApiUrl}/leads`, applicationId: siteConfig.applicationId, toast: landingContent.en.toast }}>
  (() => {
    const modal = document.querySelector("[data-lead-modal]");
    const toastEl = document.querySelector("[data-lead-toast]");
    let toastTimer, lastFocused = null;

    const showToast = (message, isError) => {
      if (!toastEl) return;
      toastEl.textContent = message;
      toastEl.classList.toggle("lead-toast--error", Boolean(isError));
      toastEl.hidden = false;
      void toastEl.offsetWidth;
      toastEl.classList.add("lead-toast--visible");
      clearTimeout(toastTimer);
      toastTimer = setTimeout(() => {
        toastEl.classList.remove("lead-toast--visible");
        setTimeout(() => { toastEl.hidden = true; }, 300);
      }, 4000);
    };

    const openModal = (from) => {
      if (!modal) return;
      const form = modal.querySelector("[data-lead-form]");
      if (form && from) form.setAttribute("data-from", from);
      lastFocused = document.activeElement;
      modal.hidden = false;
      void modal.offsetWidth;
      modal.classList.add("lead-modal--open");
      document.body.style.overflow = "hidden";
      const input = modal.querySelector("input");
      if (input) setTimeout(() => input.focus(), 50);
    };

    const closeModal = () => {
      if (!modal) return;
      modal.classList.remove("lead-modal--open");
      document.body.style.overflow = "";
      setTimeout(() => { modal.hidden = true; }, 250);
      if (lastFocused && typeof lastFocused.focus === "function") lastFocused.focus();
    };

    document.querySelectorAll("[data-modal-open]").forEach((trigger) => {
      trigger.addEventListener("click", () => openModal(trigger.getAttribute("data-from")));
    });

    if (modal) {
      modal.querySelectorAll("[data-modal-close]").forEach((el) => {
        el.addEventListener("click", closeModal);
      });
    }

    document.addEventListener("keydown", (e) => {
      if (e.key === "Escape" && modal && !modal.hidden) closeModal();
    });

    document.querySelectorAll("[data-lead-form]").forEach((form) => {
      form.addEventListener("submit", async (e) => {
        e.preventDefault();
        const input = form.querySelector('input[type="email"]');
        const button = form.querySelector('button[type="submit"]');
        const email = input ? input.value.trim() : "";
        const from = form.getAttribute("data-from") || "unknown";
        if (!input || !input.checkValidity() || !email) { if (input) input.reportValidity(); return; }
        if (button) button.disabled = true;
        form.setAttribute("aria-busy", "true");
        try {
          const res = await fetch(leadsUrl, { method: "POST", headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" }, body: JSON.stringify({ email, applicationId, metadata: { from } }) });
          if (!res.ok) throw new Error();
          if (input) input.value = "";
          if (modal && form.closest("[data-lead-modal]")) closeModal();
          showToast(toast.success, false);
        } catch {
          showToast(toast.error, true);
        } finally {
          if (button) button.disabled = false;
          form.removeAttribute("aria-busy");
        }
      });
    });
  })();
</script>

<style>
  .article-page {
    padding-top: 80px;
    background: #F3F3F3;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  .article {
    max-width: 1192px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 60px 24px 100px;
  }

  /* Header */
  .article-header {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto 40px;
  }

  .article-category {
    font-family: 'Roboto Flex', sans-serif;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #6B6B6B;
    margin: 0 0 20px;
  }

  .article-title {
    font-family: 'Roboto Flex', sans-serif;
    font-size: 42px;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: #0E0E0E;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
  }

  .article-subtitle {
    font-family: 'Roboto Flex', sans-serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: #3D3D3D;
    margin: 0 0 24px;
  }

  .article-meta {
    font-family: 'Roboto Flex', sans-serif;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: #6B6B6B;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
  }

  .article-meta-dot {
    color: #B0B0B0;
  }

  /* Hero image */
  .article-hero {
    max-width: 920px;
    margin: 0 auto 56px;
    border-radius: 16px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .article-hero img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    object-fit: cover;
    max-height: 520px;
  }

  /* Body */
  .article-body {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .article-body p {
    font-family: 'Roboto Flex', sans-serif;
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #1C1C1C;
    margin: 0 0 28px;
  }

  .article-body h2 {
    font-family: 'Roboto Flex', sans-serif;
    font-size: 28px;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.25;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: #0E0E0E;
    margin: 52px 0 16px;
  }

  .article-body h3 {
    font-family: 'Roboto Flex', sans-serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: #0E0E0E;
    margin: 36px 0 12px;
  }

  .article-body strong {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #0E0E0E;
  }

  .article-body em {
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .article-body a {
    color: #4C27E3;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: rgba(76, 39, 227, 0.35);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    transition: text-decoration-color 0.15s;
  }

  .article-body a:hover {
    text-decoration-color: #4C27E3;
  }

  .article-body button.btn-secondary {
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  .article-rule {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid #E8E8E8;
    margin: 40px 0;
  }

  .sources-title {
    font-family: 'Roboto Flex', sans-serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #6B6B6B;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
  }

  .sources-list {
    padding-left: 20px;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .sources-list li {
    font-family: 'Roboto Flex', sans-serif;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #6B6B6B;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .sources-list a {
    color: #6B6B6B;
    font-size: 13px;
    word-break: break-all;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .article {
      padding: 40px 20px 80px;
    }

    .article-title {
      font-size: 30px;
    }

    .article-subtitle {
      font-size: 18px;
    }

    .article-hero {
      margin-bottom: 40px;
    }

    .article-body p {
      font-size: 18px;
    }

    .article-body h2 {
      font-size: 24px;
      margin-top: 40px;
    }

    .article-body h3 {
      font-size: 20px;
    }
  }
</style>
